<HL>
   International Brief -- Coca-Cola Amatil Ltd.:
   Coke Affiliate to Sell Assets
   Of Its Leigh Mardon Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
09/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   KO A.KOA U.MID
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BEVERAGES (BVG)
</IN>
<LP>
   Coca-Cola Amatil Ltd. of Australia said it agreed to sell
the packaging division and communications and systems
division of its unit, Leigh Mardon Pty., to DBSM Capital
Partners Ltd. and Prudential Asset Management Asia Ltd. for
260 million Australian dollars ($US215 million).
   Coca-Cola Amatil makes almost all the Coca-Cola consumed
in Australia and is 59.5% owned by Coca-Cola Co., Atlanta.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   DBSM Capital Partners is a unit of Dominguez Barry Samuel
Montagu Ltd., an Australian investment bank that is a unit of
Midland Bank PLC.
   Coca-Cola Amatil said it expects the sale of the Leigh
Mardon units to be completed by Nov. 30, although the
agreement to sell is subject to shareholder approval.
</TEXT>
